Gamma of Mauritius Advances on Report of Strategic Alliance

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-04-20T08:39:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/gamma-of-mauritius-advances-on-report-of-strategic-alliance.html
Gamma Civic Ltd. (GML) , Mauritius’s
biggest construction company by market value, rose by the most
in two weeks after a report saying it will enter a strategic
alliance with Colas Maurice Ltd.  The stock rose 10 rupees or 2.6 percent to 400 rupees at
11:35 a.m, the biggest intraday rise since April 8.  Port Louis-based l’Express newspaper reported today that
Gamma Civic will enter into a partnership with Colas Maurice,
giving Gamma access to modern building materials. Gamma
announced on April 8 that it plans to enter into a strategic
alliance with an overseas company.  To contact the reporter on this story: Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port
Louis  via Johannesburg at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  